org.presentation.persistence.integration

Interface MessageEntityDAO

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MessageEntityDAOImpl

    public interface MessageEntityDAO
    MessageEntityDAO interface that serves as layer between business persistence facade and persistence context.
    Author:
    radio.koza

    • Method Detail

      • create

        void create(MessageEntity message)
        Method persists new MessageEntity in database. Note that message must have checkup assigned or this method will fail.
        Parameters:
        message - MessageEntity to be persisted in database

      • findAllCheckMessages

        List<MessageEntity> findAllCheckMessages(Integer checkupId)
        Method finds collection of all MessageEntity objects assigned to checkup with specified primary key.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the checkup
        Returns:
        List of MessageEntity instances; collection can be empty but never null

      • findAllCheckMessages

        List<MessageEntity> findAllCheckMessages(Integer checkupId,
                                         int offset,
                                         int count)
        Method has the same functionality as findAllCheckMessages(java.lang.Integer) but moreover supports filtering result by specifying index of first result and count of results.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the checkup
        offset - Index of the first element indexed from zero
        count - Count of the results to query
        Returns:
        List of MessageEntity assigned to the checkup with List.size() <= count

      • findAllCheckMessageResources

        List<String> findAllCheckMessageResources(Integer checkupId)
        Method lists all distinct resource names of checkup specified by primary key.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the checkup
        Returns:
        Collection of distinct message producer names

      • findAllCheckMessagesFromResource

        List<MessageEntity> findAllCheckMessagesFromResource(Integer checkupId,
                                                     String resource)
        Method finds collection of MessageEntity objects with specified message producer assigned to checkup specified by primary key.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the checkup
        resource - Name of the message producer
        Returns:
        List of the MessageEntity instances

      • findAllCheckMessagesFromResource

                                                     int offset,
                                                     int count)
        Method has the same functionality as findAllCheckMessagesFromResource(java.lang.Integer, java.lang.String) but moreover supports filtering results by specifying index of first result and count of results.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the checkup
        resource - Name of the message producer
        offset - Index of the first element indexed from zero
        count - Count of the results to query
        Returns:
        List of MessageEntity assigned to the checkup with List.size() <= count

      • findAllCheckMessagesFromResources

        List<MessageEntity> findAllCheckMessagesFromResources(Integer checkupId,
                                                      List<String> resources)
        Method has the same functionality as findAllCheckMessagesFromResource(java.lang.Integer, java.lang.String) but supports multiple message producer names filtering.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the checkup
        resources - Collection of wanted message producer names
        Returns:
        List of MessageEntity matching the filter

      • countCheckMessages

        int countCheckMessages(Integer checkupId)

        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the checkup
        Returns:
        Count of the messages

      • countCheckMessagesFromResources

        int countCheckMessagesFromResources(Integer checkupId,
                                    List<String> resources)
        Method counts MessageEntity objects matching one of specified message producer names assigned to checkup specified by its primary key.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the specified checkup
        resources - Collection of wanted message producer names
        Returns:
        Count of the MessageEntity instances matching the filter

      • countCheckMessagesByDiscriminators

        int countCheckMessagesByDiscriminators(Integer checkupId,
                                       List<String> discriminators)
        Method counts MessageEntity objects matching one of specified message discriminator names assigned to checkup specified by its primary key.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the specified checkup
        discriminators - Collection of wanted message discriminators (discriminator is fully qualified class name of Message abstract class implementation)
        Returns:
        Count of the MessageEntity instances matching the filter

      • countCheckMessagesByResourcesDiscriminators

        int countCheckMessagesByResourcesDiscriminators(Integer checkupId,
                                                List<String> resources,
                                                List<String> discriminators)
        Method merges functionality of countCheckMessagesFromResources(java.lang.Integer, java.util.List) and countCheckMessagesByDiscriminators(java.lang.Integer, java.util.List). Merge is made by usage of logical conjunction.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the checkup
        resources - Collection of wanted message producer names
        discriminators - Collection of wanted message discriminators (discriminator is fully qualified class name of Message abstract class)
        Returns:
        Count of the MessageEntity instances matching the filter

      • findAllCheckMessagesByDiscriminators

        List<MessageEntity> findAllCheckMessagesByDiscriminators(Integer checkupId,
                                                         List<String> discriminators)
        Method finds all MessageEntity objects of checkup specified by its primary key with one of specified message discriminator names.
        Parameters:
        checkupId - Primary key of the checkup
        discriminators - Collection of wanted message discriminators (discriminator is fully qualified class name of Message abstract class)
        Returns:
        List of MessageEntity instances matching the filter
